  "markdown": "[Skip to main content](https://9to5google.com/2026/04/06/samsung-weather-app-updates-tweaks-pollen/#main)\n\n- [Samsung](https://9to5google.com/guides/samsung/)\n\n# Samsung’s updated Weather app is ready to tell you how horrible the pollen is outside\n\n[![Avatar for Ben Schoon](https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/59cb0e121a572a78cfc8040731068741887591b7ef93f5498a8d93310278c0f7?s=30&d=mm&r=r)](https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/) [Ben Schoon](https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/ \"Posts by Ben Schoon\") \\| Apr 6 2026 - 7:35 am PT\n\n[0 Comments](https://9to5google.com/2026/04/06/samsung-weather-app-updates-tweaks-pollen/#comments)\n\n![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2025/12/Samsung-Weather-pollen-count-2.jpg?quality=82&strip=all&w=1600)\n\nAs Spring has sprung, The Pollening has also arrived and, just in time, Samsung has made some welcome updates to its Weather app.\n\nThe Samsung Weather app sees UI updates fairly regularly, and another new tweak is arriving in the v1.7.30.8.\n\nAs the folks at _[Android Authority](https://www.androidauthority.com/samsung-weather-app-update-ui-changes-3654799/)_ first pointed out, the new update to Samsung Weather brings an improvement for those suffering through pollen allergies. Specifically, the app has ditched its generic leaf icons for pollen and now shows icons for tree, grass, and ragweed pollen measurements that are easy to identify at a glance. That said, it also removes the colored scale for pollen intensity, replacing that with just a word. So, perhaps a lateral move in some ways.\n\nThe app sees a few other icon changes to moon phases and radar, with the latter now showing some more shortcuts that open to [weather.com](http://weather.com/)‘s forecasting tools.\n\nAdvertisement - scroll for more content\n\n![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/04/samsung-weather-app-updates-1.webp?w=461)_Old_![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/04/samsung-weather-app-updates-2.webp?w=461)_New pollen icons_![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/04/samsung-weather-app-updates-4.webp)![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/04/samsung-weather-app-updates-3.webp?w=461)\n\nThese changes are live in Samsung Weather Widget – that’s the full name of the app – v1.7.30.8, though you might not have that update available in the Galaxy Store right away. The update seems to be only for One UI 8.5.\n\nPollen features remain available in Samsung Weather even if you’re not on One UI 8.5, though, in the latest Samsung Weather updates on One UI 8.0.\n\n## More on Samsung:\n\n- [Galaxy S27 ‘Pro’ reportedly packs Ultra specs, maybe cameras, as a fourth model](https://9to5google.com/2026/04/06/samsung-galaxy-s27-pro-report/)\n- [Google Cast support rolling out to Samsung TVs, and not just the newest ones](https://9to5google.com/2026/04/02/google-cast-support-rolling-out-to-samsung-tvs-and-not-just-the-newest-ones/)\n- [Samsung quietly removed third-party font support from devices running One UI 8.5](https://9to5google.com/2026/03/31/samsung-quietly-removed-third-party-font-support-one-ui-8-5/)\n\n_**Follow Ben:** [Twitter/X](https://twitter.com/NexusBen), [Threads](https://www.threads.net/@nexusben), [Bluesky](https://bsky.app/profile/nexusben.com), and [Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/nexusben)_\n\n[![Add 9to5Google as a preferred source on Google](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/themes/ninetofive/dist/images/google-preferred-source-badge-dark.png)![Add 9to5Google as a preferred source on Google](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/themes/ninetofive/dist/images/google-preferred-source-badge-light.png)](https://google.com/preferences/source?q=https://9to5google.com)\n\n_FTC: We use income earning auto affiliate links._ [More.](https://9to5mac.com/about/#affiliate)\n\n[![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/04/750x150-1.jpg?quality=82&strip=all&w=700)](https://bit.ly/4dZciVW)\n\nYou’re reading 9to5Google — experts who break news about Google and its surrounding ecosystem, day after day. Be sure to check out [our homepage](http://9to5google.com/) for all the latest news, and follow 9to5Google on [Twitter](http://twitter.com/9to5google), [Facebook](http://facebook.com/9to5google), and [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/9to5google.com/) to stay in the loop. Don’t know where to start? Check out our [exclusive stories](https://9to5google.com/feature/exclusive/), [reviews](https://9to5google.com/guides/reviews/), [how-tos](https://9to5google.com/guides/how-to/), and [subscribe to our YouTube channel](https://www.youtube.com/9to5google)\n\n[_Check out 9to5Google on YouTube for more news:_](https://www.youtube.com/c/9to5google?sub_confirmation=1)\n\n## Comments\n\nExpandClose comments\n\nExpandClose comments\n\n## Guides\n\n[![Samsung](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2020/02/samsung_logo_1.jpg?quality=82&strip=all&w=140)\\\\\n\\\\\n**Samsung** \\\\\n\\\\\nSamsung is a technology conglomerate based out o…](https://9to5google.com/guides/samsung/)\n\n## Author\n\n[![Avatar for Ben Schoon](https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/59cb0e121a572a78cfc8040731068741887591b7ef93f5498a8d93310278c0f7?s=82&d=mm&r=r)](https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/)[Ben Schoon](https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/) [nexusben](https://twitter.com/intent/follow?screen_name=nexusben&original_referer=https%3A%2F%2F9to5google.com)\n\nBen is a Senior Editor for 9to5Google.\n\nFind him on Twitter @NexusBen. Send tips to schoon@9to5g.com or encrypted to benschoon@protonmail.com.\n\n![](https://9to5google.com/2026/04/06/samsung-weather-app-updates-tweaks-pollen/)\n\n![](https://9to5google.com/2026/04/06/samsung-weather-app-updates-tweaks-pollen/)\n\nSubscribe to notifications",
